                    <ul class="instructions__inner">
                      <li id="step1" class="instructions__contents ss-align--center">
                        <img src="../../../docs/images/ico-send.svg" height="100" alt="image of paper plane flying through the air">
                        <h2 class="instructions__heading">Step 1 - Submit this claim</h2>
                        <p class="instructions__txt">Mental health treatment is available for free under our Non-Liability Health Care arrangements. You do not need to show a link to service to qualify for free
                          mental&nbsp;health&nbsp;treatment.
                        </p>
                        <p class="instructions__txt">All you need to do is submit this claim.</p>
                      </li>
                      <li id="step2" class="instructions__contents ss-align--center" style="display:none;">
                        <img src="../../../docs/images/ico-healthcard.svg" height="100" alt="image of a digital health card">
                        <h2 class="instructions__heading">Step 2 - Receive a DVA Health Card</h2>
                        <p class="instructions__txt">After your claim is processed, we will send you a DVA Health Card (White&nbsp;Card). The accepted condition 'Mental Health Treatment (NLHC)' will be listed on
                          your&nbsp;card.</p>
                        <p class="instructions__txt">You can access a digital version of your card in&nbsp;MyService.</p>
                      </li>
                      <li id="step3" class="instructions__contents ss-align--center" style="display:none;">
                        <img src="../../../docs/images/ico-handshake.svg" height="100" alt="image of shaking hands">
                        <h2 class="instructions__heading">Step 3 - Get treatment</h2>
                        <p class="instructions__txt">Your DVA Health Card works like a Medicare card. Show your card to your treatment provider and they will bill DVA for the cost of&nbsp;the&nbsp;treatment.</p>
                        <p class="instructions__txt">The digital Health Card is still quite new, so check with your health care provider before your appointment to make sure they can accept&nbsp;it.</p>
                        <p class="instructions__txt">If you end up paying for the cost of your mental health treatment, keep your receipts. You can claim for reimbursement using&nbsp;MyAccount.</p>
                      </li>
                      <li id="step4" class="instructions__contents ss-align--center" style="display:none;">
                        <img src="../../../docs/images/ico-umbrella.svg" height="100" alt="image of an umbrella">
                        <h2 class="instructions__heading">Step 4 - Know what you're covered for</h2>
                        <p class="instructions__txt">Treatment for all mental health conditions are covered.</p>
                        <p class="instructions__txt">This includes treatment from a general practitioner, medical specialist, psychologist, social worker, occupational therapist, psychiatrist, hospital services,
                          specialist PTSD programs, pharmaceuticals, or oncologist services&nbsp;as&nbsp;required.</p>
                      </li>
                    </ul>
                    <div id="help-pagination" class="instructions__contents instructions__contents--pagination ss-align--center margin-below">
                      <button id="arrow-back" class="uikit-btn uikit-btn--tertiary">Previous</button>
                      <button id="arrow-next" class="uikit-btn">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Next&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</button>
